status: Indicates the audience for which the item is intended.

definition (en): Target audience for which the material is intended is unknown or is not specified.
Aimed at a particular audience and the nature of the presentation would make the item of little interest to other audiences.
scope note (en): Examples include: 1) technical material geared to a specialized audience, and 2) items which address a limited audience; for example, the employees of a single organization.

definition (en): Of general interest and not aimed at a particular target audience.
Children and young people, approximate ages 0-15.
